"<!-- Generated by Skillsmith. Scope: project. Re-run: skillsmith . --yes -->

# Project Overview

This repository is a **web-app** written primarily in **TypeScript**, built with **Next.js 14 App Router**. Use the paths and patterns below as ground truth when editing code—prefer extending existing abstractions over inventing new ones.

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14 App Router
- **Package manager:** pnpm
- **Testing:** Vitest
- **Key libraries:** next, react, tailwindcss, @radix-ui/react-slot, class-variance-authority, clsx, tailwind-merge

## Commands

### Install

\`\`\`bash
pnpm install
\`\`\`

### Dev server

\`\`\`bash
pnpm dev
\`\`\`

### Build

\`\`\`bash
pnpm build
\`\`\`

### Test (full suite)

\`\`\`bash
pnpm test
\`\`\`

### Test (single path)

\`\`\`bash
pnpm test -- <path>
\`\`\`

### Lint

\`\`\`bash
pnpm lint
\`\`\`


## Conventions

### Naming

- **Files:** Kebab-case for \`app/\` route segments; PascalCase for components under \`components/\`. Colocate feature modules under \`features/<name>/\`.
- **Components:** PascalCase file names matching the default export. Prefer composing primitives from \`components/ui/\` (shadcn) rather than one-off styled divs.
- **Functions:** camelCase for utilities and hooks (\`useTheme\`). Event handlers prefixed with \`handle\` or passed as \`onX\` props.
- **Variables:** camelCase locals; SCREAMING_SNAKE only for true constants. Prefer \`const\` and narrow types with \`satisfies\` where helpful.

### Layout and architecture

Routes and layouts live in \`app/\` (App Router). Shared UI primitives live in \`components/ui/\` (shadcn). Shared helpers in \`lib/\` (e.g. \`lib/utils.ts\` with \`cn()\`). Global styles in \`app/globals.css\`; Tailwind v4 via \`@tailwindcss/postcss\`.

### Errors, state, and tests

- **Error handling:** Use \`try/catch\` in Server Actions and surface user-facing errors with Sonner toasts on the client. Prefer returning typed Result-like objects from server utilities when batching work.
- **State:** React state and context for local UI; server state from \`fetch\` in Server Components. No global client store unless a route truly needs it.
- **Testing:** Vitest + Testing Library for components; colocate \`*.test.tsx\` next to components or under \`__tests__/\`. Run \`pnpm test\` from repo root.

## Key Patterns

### cn() helper

\`lib/utils.ts\` — Merge Tailwind classes with \`tailwind-merge\` to avoid conflicting utilities.

\`\`\`tsx
// Example: import or compose from lib/utils.ts
\`\`\`

### Button variants

\`components/ui/button.tsx\` — Use \`class-variance-authority\` (cva) for size and variant props on shadcn \`Button\`.

\`\`\`tsx
// Example: import or compose from components/ui/button.tsx
\`\`\`

### App layout shell

\`app/layout.tsx\` — Root layout wraps providers (\`ThemeProvider\`, \`Toaster\`) and font loading.

\`\`\`tsx
// Example: import or compose from app/layout.tsx
\`\`\`

## Things to Avoid

- Do not hand-edit \`components.json\` or generated shadcn files without running the CLI.
- Avoid fetching in Client Components when the same data can be loaded in a Server Component.
- Do not add new CSS files per page; extend Tailwind tokens or use \`cn()\` instead.

## Common Tasks

Typical workflow: **Add a shadcn UI primitive**

- Run \`pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>\` from the repo root.
- Import from \`@/components/ui/<component>\` in your feature code.
- Use \`cn()\` from \`@/lib/utils\` when merging classes.
- Run \`pnpm lint\` and \`pnpm test\` before opening a PR.
"
